{
  "texts": [
    "It can be challenging to construct a validation dataset due to the currently unclear evaluation metrics for FM performance.",
    "The huge scales of FMs and the corresponding datasets also make effective evaluation of local model updates costly.Hybrid Schemes: Research works have emerged [122]- [124] in an attempt to form hybrids schemes to take advantages of the aforementioned by combining them together.",
    "These works often update a benchmark model with a central clean dataset, and lower the weights assigned to local model updates that significantly deviate from the benchmark (or even discard them completely) during aggregation.",
    "Although these methods have achieved superior robustness, they have also inherited the limitations from the aforementioned categories of approaches which make them incompatible with the FedFM settings.",
    "B. Privacy of FedFMPrivacy preservation has always been a central focus of FL research."
  ]
}